tag.notes:
If you want to enable CCPA and are not on a monthly paid Elevar plan then the DIY approach is:

1. Create an opt-out CCPA form on your website following CCPA guidelines
2. Update the variable named NEEDS UPDATING - JS - CCPA Opt-Out Selected to match the form element for your form created in step 1
3. Update the trigger named NEEDS UPDATING - Form - CCPA Out-Out - to use the page path your form is hosted on
4. Update your sitewide FB pixel to include the following line:

if ({{CCPA Cookie}}){
  fbq('dataProcessingOptions', ['LDU'], 1, 1000);
}
else {
  fbq('dataProcessingOptions', []);
}

It should look similar to screenshot shown in this guide - https://www.getelevar.com/gtm/facebook-pixel-ccpa-compliance-shopify/

To Do's:

1) Update the conversion label to match the conversion label from your Google Ads conversion

2) The product level sales data is optional. If you'd like to enable then you have to update the merchant center variables which you can reference how to find those here: https://support.google.com/google-ads/answer/9028614?hl=en

The data layer variables for discount and item inputs are:

{{dlv - Thank You Page - Discount Amount}}

{{js - Google Ads - Purchase Product Data}}

